               Abstract
               
                  The hydration of nickel ions in a 3.80 molal solution of nickel perchlorate in (heavy) water has been investigated by the neutron first-order difference method. The coordination of water molecules around nickel ions is identical with that found in an earlier study of a nickel chloride solution of comparable ionic strength.
               
